    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - PAINT AND REFINISHING - PAINT - BINDER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>BINDER</title>
        <para>Binder is the film former. It holds the pigment in liquid form, makes it durable, and gives it the ability
            to stick to the surface. It is the backbone of paint. The binder generally is made up of a synthetic resin.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
